  {
    "type": "math",
    "content": "\\frac{d}{dx}\\left[x^{-2}\\right] = -2 \\cdot x^{-2-1} = -2x^{-3}",
    "narration": "The exponent, negative 2, becomes the multiplier. Then we subtract 1 from the exponent \u2014 negative 2 minus 1 is negative 3. That gives us negative 2 x to the negative 3.",
    "mode": "replace",
    "layout": {
      "scale": 1.1
    },
    "step": 2,
    "audio_path": "/Users/claudioatlas/Desktop/Orbital/orbital_factory/jobs/short_power_rule_with_negative_exponents/audio/step_02.mp3",
    "duration": 15.443
  },
  {
    "type": "math",
    "content": "-2x^{-3} = \\frac{-2}{x^3}",
    "narration": "A negative exponent means x moves to the denominator. So negative 2 x to the negative 3 rewrites as negative 2 over x cubed. That's your final answer.",
    "mode": "replace",
    "layout": {
      "scale": 1.5
    },
    "step": 3,
